[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] To other analysts the delay between CRA rule changes in 1995 and the explosion of subprime lending is not surprising, and does not exonerate the CRA.
[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] They contend that there were two, connected causes to the crisis: the relaxation of underwriting standards in 1995 and the ultra-low interest rates initiated by the Federal Reserve after the terrorist attack on September 11, 2001.
[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] Both causes had to be in place before the crisis could take place.
[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] Critics also point out that publicly announced CRA loan commitments were massive, totaling $4.5 trillion in the years between 1994 and 2007.
