[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] The Congressional Budget Office estimated, in June 2011, that the bailout to Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac exceeds $300 billion (c. $411 billion in 2024) (calculated by adding the fair value deficits of the entities to the direct bailout funds at the time).
[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] In other words, bubbles in both markets developed even though only the residential market was affected by these potential causes.
