[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] Between 1998 and 2006, the price of the typical American house increased by 124%.
[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] During the 1980s and 1990s, the national median home price ranged from 2.9 to 3.1 times median household income.
[src:abandoned-pets/2008-financial-crisis-p02] By contrast, this ratio increased to 4.0 in 2004, and 4.6 in 2006.
